{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":785,"text":"What if I could present you a story"},{"time":2689,"text":"that you would remember\nwith your entire body"},{"time":5127,"text":"and not just with your mind?"},{"time":7308,"text":"My whole life as a journalist,\nI've really been compelled"},{"time":10007,"text":"to try to make stories\nthat can make a difference"},{"time":12342,"text":"and maybe inspire people to care."},{"time":14936,"text":"I've worked in print.\nI've worked in documentary."},{"time":17286,"text":"I've worked in broadcast."},{"time":18579,"text":"But it really wasn't until\nI got involved with virtual reality"},{"time":21665,"text":"that I started seeing\nthese really intense,"},{"time":24530,"text":"authentic reactions from people"},{"time":26538,"text":"that really blew my mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28237,"text":"So the deal is that with VR,\nvirtual reality,"},{"time":32934,"text":"I can put you on scene"},{"time":35958,"text":"in the middle of the story."},{"time":38148,"text":"By putting on these goggles\nthat track wherever you look,"},{"time":41656,"text":"you get this whole-body sensation,"},{"time":44608,"text":"like you're actually, like, there."},{"time":47209,"text":"So five years ago was about when\nI really began to push the envelope"},{"time":50635,"text":"with using virtual reality\nand journalism together."},{"time":53909,"text":"And I wanted to do a piece about hunger."},{"time":56481,"text":"Families in America are going hungry,\nfood banks are overwhelmed,"},{"time":59664,"text":"and they're often running out of food."},{"time":62330,"text":"Now, I knew I couldn't\nmake people feel hungry,"},{"time":65973,"text":"but maybe I could figure out a way\nto get them to feel something physical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70726,"text":"So -- again, this is five years ago --"},{"time":73814,"text":"so doing journalism\nand virtual reality together"},{"time":77014,"text":"was considered\na worse-than-half-baked idea,"},{"time":80021,"text":"and I had no funding."},{"time":81400,"text":"Believe me, I had a lot\nof colleagues laughing at me."},{"time":83923,"text":"And I did, though,\nhave a really great intern,"},{"time":87737,"text":"a woman named Michaela Kobsa-Mark."},{"time":89999,"text":"And together we went out to food banks"},{"time":91841,"text":"and started recording\naudio and photographs."},{"time":94937,"text":"Until one day she came back to my office"},{"time":96881,"text":"and she was bawling, she was just crying."},{"time":99300,"text":"She had been on scene at a long line,"},{"time":101926,"text":"where the woman running the line\nwas feeling extremely overwhelmed,"},{"time":105895,"text":"and she was screaming,\n\"There's too many people!"},{"time":108887,"text":"There's too many people!\""},{"time":110807,"text":"And this man with diabetes\ndoesn't get food in time,"},{"time":114386,"text":"his blood sugar drops too low,\nand he collapses into a coma."},{"time":118695,"text":"As soon as I heard that audio,"},{"time":120251,"text":"I knew that this would be\nthe kind of evocative piece"},{"time":123520,"text":"that could really describe\nwhat was going on at food banks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127290,"text":"So here's the real line.\nYou can see how long it was, right?"},{"time":130930,"text":"And again, as I said, we didn't\nhave very much funding,"},{"time":133581,"text":"so I had to reproduce it\nwith virtual humans that were donated,"},{"time":137355,"text":"and people begged and borrowed favors\nto help me create the models"},{"time":141505,"text":"and make things as accurate as we could."},{"time":143688,"text":"And then we tried to convey\nwhat happened that day"},{"time":146321,"text":"with as much as accuracy as is possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149680,"text":"(Video) Voice: There's too many people!\nThere's too many people!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162340,"text":"Voice: OK, he's having a seizure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179023,"text":"Voice: We need an ambulance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182181,"text":"Nonny de la Pe√±a: So the man on the right,"},{"time":184222,"text":"for him, he's walking around the body."},{"time":186118,"text":"For him, he's in the room with that body."},{"time":189355,"text":"Like, that guy is at his feet."},{"time":191601,"text":"And even though,\nthrough his peripheral vision,"},{"time":193832,"text":"he can see that he's in this lab space,"},{"time":195927,"text":"he should be able to see\nthat he's not actually on the street,"},{"time":200164,"text":"but he feels like he's there\nwith those people."},{"time":203084,"text":"He's very cautious not to step on this guy"},{"time":205118,"text":"who isn't really there, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207506,"text":"So that piece ended up\ngoing to Sundance in 2012,"},{"time":210633,"text":"a kind of amazing thing,\nand it was the first virtual reality film"},{"time":214578,"text":"ever, basically."},{"time":217062,"text":"And when we went, I was really terrified."},{"time":219047,"text":"I didn't really know\nhow people were going to react"},{"time":221508,"text":"and what was going to happen."},{"time":222921,"text":"And we showed up\nwith this duct-taped pair of goggles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225842,"text":"(Video) Oh, you're crying.\nYou're crying. Gina, you're crying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229851,"text":"So you can hear\nthe surprise in my voice, right?"},{"time":232595,"text":"And this kind of reaction ended up being\nthe kind of reaction we saw"},{"time":236214,"text":"over and over and over:"},{"time":239008,"text":"people down on the ground\ntrying to comfort the seizure victim,"},{"time":242738,"text":"trying to whisper something into his ear"},{"time":244682,"text":"or in some way help,\neven though they couldn't."},{"time":248664,"text":"And I had a lot of people\ncome out of that piece saying,"},{"time":251372,"text":"\"Oh my God, I was so frustrated.\nI couldn't help the guy,\""},{"time":254120,"text":"and take that back into their lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256999,"text":"So after this piece was made,"},{"time":260198,"text":"the dean of the cinema school at USC,\nthe University of Southern California,"},{"time":264031,"text":"brought in the head of the World\nEconomic Forum to try \"Hunger,\""},{"time":268262,"text":"and he took off the goggles,"},{"time":269627,"text":"and he commissioned\na piece about Syria on the spot."},{"time":272691,"text":"And I really wanted to do something\nabout Syrian refugee kids,"},{"time":275628,"text":"because children have been the worst\naffected by the Syrian civil war."},{"time":280809,"text":"I sent a team to the border of Iraq\nto record material at refugee camps,"},{"time":284791,"text":"basically an area I wouldn't\nsend a team now,"},{"time":287966,"text":"as that's where ISIS is really operating."},{"time":290458,"text":"And then we also recreated a street scene"},{"time":293188,"text":"in which a young girl is singing\nand a bomb goes off."},{"time":297340,"text":"Now, when you're\nin the middle of that scene"},{"time":299443,"text":"and you hear those sounds,"},{"time":302021,"text":"and you see the injured around you,"},{"time":304338,"text":"it's an incredibly scary and real feeling."},{"time":307362,"text":"I've had individuals who have been\ninvolved in real bombings tell me"},{"time":311926,"text":"that it evokes the same kind of fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316211,"text":"[The civil war in Syria may seem far away]"},{"time":322078,"text":"[until you experience it yourself.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":329062,"text":"(Girl singing)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336037,"text":"(Explosion)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338839,"text":"[Project Syria]"},{"time":343988,"text":"[A virtual reality experience]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":346653,"text":"NP: We were then invited to take the piece"},{"time":348745,"text":"to the Victoria and Albert\nMuseum in London."},{"time":350823,"text":"And it wasn't advertised."},{"time":352204,"text":"And we were put in this tapestry room."},{"time":354552,"text":"There was no press about it,"},{"time":355918,"text":"so anybody who happened to walk\ninto the museum to visit it that day"},{"time":359679,"text":"would see us with these crazy lights."},{"time":361466,"text":"You know, maybe they would want to see\nthe old storytelling of the tapestries."},{"time":365165,"text":"They were confronted\nby our virtual reality cameras."},{"time":368513,"text":"But a lot of people tried it,\nand over a five-day run"},{"time":371664,"text":"we ended up with 54 pages\nof guest book comments,"},{"time":376228,"text":"and we were told by the curators there"},{"time":378588,"text":"that they'd never seen such an outpouring."},{"time":381201,"text":"Things like, \"It's so real,\"\n\"Absolutely believable,\""},{"time":385852,"text":"or, of course, the one\nthat I was excited about,"},{"time":388336,"text":"\"A real feeling as if you were\nin the middle of something"},{"time":391209,"text":"that you normally see on the TV news.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":394463,"text":"So, it works, right? This stuff works."},{"time":398297,"text":"And it doesn't really matter\nwhere you're from or what age you are --"},{"time":402116,"text":"it's really evocative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404343,"text":"Now, don't get me wrong -- I'm not saying\nthat when you're in a piece"},{"time":408319,"text":"you forget that you're here."},{"time":411223,"text":"But it turns out we can feel\nlike we're in two places at once."},{"time":414422,"text":"We can have what I call\nthis duality of presence,"},{"time":417596,"text":"and I think that's what allows me\nto tap into these feelings of empathy."},{"time":422477,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":424041,"text":"So that means, of course,"},{"time":427256,"text":"that I have to be very cautious\nabout creating these pieces."},{"time":432175,"text":"I have to really follow\nbest journalistic practices"},{"time":436461,"text":"and make sure that these powerful stories"},{"time":438620,"text":"are built with integrity."},{"time":440230,"text":"If we don't capture\nthe material ourselves,"},{"time":442627,"text":"we have to be extremely exacting"},{"time":447619,"text":"about figuring out the provenance\nand where did this stuff come from"},{"time":450944,"text":"and is it authentic?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452276,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":453657,"text":"With this Trayvon Martin case,\nthis is a guy, a kid,"},{"time":456618,"text":"who was 17 years old and he bought\nsoda and a candy at a store,"},{"time":460745,"text":"and on his way home he was tracked\nby a neighborhood watchman"},{"time":464245,"text":"named George Zimmerman\nwho ended up shooting and killing him."},{"time":467657,"text":"To make that piece,"},{"time":468833,"text":"we got the architectural drawings\nof the entire complex,"},{"time":472459,"text":"and we rebuilt the entire scene\ninside and out, based on those drawings."},{"time":477252,"text":"All of the action"},{"time":478571,"text":"is informed by the real 911\nrecorded calls to the police."},{"time":484411,"text":"And interestingly, we broke\nsome news with this story."},{"time":487212,"text":"The forensic house that did the audio\nreconstruction, Primeau Productions,"},{"time":491211,"text":"they say that they would testify"},{"time":493181,"text":"that George Zimmerman,\nwhen he got out of the car,"},{"time":495880,"text":"he cocked his gun before he went\nto give chase to Martin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500013,"text":"So you can see that\nthe basic tenets of journalism,"},{"time":503442,"text":"they don't really change here, right?"},{"time":505339,"text":"We're still following the same principles\nthat we would always."},{"time":508767,"text":"What is different is the sense\nof being on scene,"},{"time":512094,"text":"whether you're watching\na guy collapse from hunger"},{"time":514459,"text":"or feeling like you're\nin the middle of a bomb scene."},{"time":516968,"text":"And this is kind of what has driven me\nforward with these pieces,"},{"time":521940,"text":"and thinking about how to make them."},{"time":523687,"text":"We're trying to make this, obviously,\nbeyond the headset, more available."},{"time":527906,"text":"We're creating mobile pieces\nlike the Trayvon Martin piece."},{"time":530857,"text":"And these things have had impact."},{"time":534430,"text":"I've had Americans tell me\nthat they've donated,"},{"time":537026,"text":"direct deductions from their bank account,\nmoney to go to Syrian children refugees."},{"time":541444,"text":"And \"Hunger in LA,\" well,\nit's helped start"},{"time":543801,"text":"a new form of doing journalism"},{"time":546254,"text":"that I think is going to join\nall the other normal platforms"},{"time":549374,"text":"in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550549,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551737,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}